This paper is primarily focused on database indexing and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Database). It also involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper discusses the use of queries as hints for reorganizing data, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the need for a dynamic component to choose the appropriate algorithm for a query, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE).
